title: Harry and Meghan asked to leave Frogmore Cottage, spokesperson said
description: Prince Harry and Meghan, the Duchess of Sussex, are no longer welcomed at their British residence, Frogmore Cottage, according to the couple’s press secretary.

title: Israel should 'erase' Palestinian village, minister says after settler rampage
description: A senior Israeli official has called for the state to “erase” the Palestinian town of Hawara, which was the site of a settler rampage over the weekend.

title: On its first day free of masks, Hong Kong is in no rush to take them off
description: On Wednesday, for the first time in almost 1,000 days, the people of Hong Kong were legally allowed to go outside without wearing masks.

title: With its energy grid under fire, some in Ukraine turn to small-scale renewables
description: As Russia’s assault continues, several nonprofits in Ukraine are working to fill energy gaps — caused either by attacks on the energy grid or broader energy shortages — with renewable infrastructure.

title: Finland's parliament overwhelmingly backs bid to join NATO
description: Finland’s parliament on Wednesday overwhelmingly backed its bid to join NATO, the assembly’s speaker said.

title: Man found carrying around a mummified corpse up to 800 years old in a food delivery bag in Peru
description: A mummified corpse up to 800 years old was found in a food delivery bag in Peru, authorities in the South American country have said.

title: Ancient restaurant highlights Iraq’s archeology renaissance
description: BAGHDAD — An international archeological mission has uncovered the remnants of what is believed to be a 5,000-year-old restaurant or tavern in the ancient city of Lagash in southern Iraq.

title: What could Chinese artillery and ammunition mean for Putin's war in Ukraine?
description: China sending artillery and ammunition to Russia could be a crucial boost for the Kremlin's hopes of battlefield success in the war's second year, military analysts told NBC News

title: Israelis step up protests over government’s legal overhaul
description: Israelis protesting a plan to overhaul the judicial system were set for large demonstrations in what protest leaders have dubbed a “national day of disruption.”

title: Ruling party candidate wins disputed election in Nigeria
description: The ruling party candidate, Bola Tinubu, was declared president-elect of Nigeria after a weekend election that opposition parties disputed.

title: At least 60 injured after a passenger train collided with a freight train in Greece
description: THESSALONIKI, Greece — A passenger train collided with an oncoming freight train in northern Greece early Wednesday, causing fires and leaving dozens injured, police and Fire Service officials said.

title: A rare look inside Crimea, the territory illegally annexed by Russia in 2014
description: Russia illegally annexed Crimea, a portion of Ukraine, back in 2014, but now Ukrainian President Zelenskyy is determined to get it back. NBC News’ Keir Simmons has a rare inside look inside Crimea and speaks with residents there.
